<br>
The Wrath of Men by Trebor &quot;Drag-o-war&quot; Kainotna    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">This deck powers Aragorn and Boromir so they can block minions and, most of <br>
the time, kill them. By giving Aragorn Ranger&#39;s Sword, Great Shield, and <br>
Coat of Mail, he is 10 attack, can only be overwhelmed by 30 or<br>
higher attack, and lowers the minion archery total by one. Give Boromir <br>
Great Shield and Coat of Mail, and can only be overwhelmed by 21 or<br>
higher attack and lowers  the minion archery total by one. Swordsman of the <br>
Northern Kingdom and Swordarm of the White Tower helps Aragorn and Boromir<br>
just in case. Legolas is their to lower the opposing minions vitality and also for <br>
blocking. Elrond heals companions. Hobbit Sword and Bounder protects Frodo <br>
and Sam. <br>
<br>
The Shadow stategy is to overwhelm the companions with Uruk-Hai so that Frodo <br>
will have to block somone also. Sauruman and Uruk Guard give the <br>
Free Peoples less choices to block. Saruman&#39;s Chill hurts the Hobbits and <br>
Uruk Shaman heals the Uruk-Hai. The RingWraiths try to add as many burdens <br>
as they can. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
